parameters.name: FHeDU
parameters.description: FHeDU:UniDirectional Differential He Flux,  0.06-0.9 MeV, one record per spin binned by pitch angle in 17 bins  (as energy-angle displays)

parameters.name: FHeDU_byE_atA
parameters.description: ---> Spectrograms by energy at sample pitch angles

parameters.name: FHeDU_ByA_atE
parameters.description: ---> Spectrograms by pitch angle at sample energies

parameters.name: FHeDU_Error
parameters.description: The Poisson statistical counting percentage error of the measurement for each energy channel and bin calculated as 1/sqrt(Counts)*100.

parameters.name: FHeDU_Error_byE_atA
parameters.description: ---> Spectrograms by energy at sample pitch angles

parameters.name: FHeDU_Error_ByA_atE
parameters.description: ---> Spectrograms by pitch angle at sample energies

parameters.name: FHeDU_Quality
parameters.description: Quality flag for the measurement for each pitch angle bin/timestep. .see PREBM standards for definition

parameters.name: FHeDU_Quality_byE_atA
parameters.description: ---> Spectrograms by energy at sample pitch angles

parameters.name: FHeDU_Quality_ByA_atE
parameters.description: ---> Spectrograms by pitch angle at sample energies

parameters.name: FHeDU_PerpPressure
parameters.description: Calculated Helium perpendicular partial pressure for energies: 60Kev-590KeV.  Does not include noisy energy channels.

parameters.name: FHeDU_ParaPressure
parameters.description: Calculated Helium parallel partial pressure for energies: 60Kev-590KeV.  Does not include noisy energy channels.

parameters.name: FHeDU_Density
parameters.description: The Number Density (#/cm^3) calculated by integrating the distribution function over energy (60Kev-590KeV) and pitch angle for Helium. Does not include noisy energy channels.

parameters.name: FHeDU_IntegralFlux
parameters.description: Pitch Angle Integrated and Energy Integrated total intensity of Helium observed during the spin for energies: 60kev-590keV. Does not include noisy energy channels.

parameters.name: FHeDU_OmniFlux
parameters.description: Omni Directional Total Helium Flux per spin for energies: 60keV-590keV (Counts/(MeV-s-cm^2))

parameters.name: FHeDU_MinimFlux
parameters.description: ---> Observed minimum intensity in the spin for each energy channel measured (60keV-590keV): Counts/(MeV-cm^2-s)

parameters.name: FHeDU_MaximFlux
parameters.description: ---> Observed maximum intensity in the spin for each energy channel measured (60keV-590keV): Counts/(MeV-cm^2-s)

parameters.name: Position
parameters.description: Position of the SC in the GEO Reference Frame.

parameters.name: Position_SM
parameters.description: ---> Position of the spacecraft in SM coordinates

parameters.name: Position_GSM
parameters.description: ---> Position of the SC in the GSM Reference Frame.

parameters.name: Position_Quality
parameters.description: ---> The position quality flag, 0=good, 1=bad.

parameters.name: OrbitNumber
parameters.description: Orbit Number at the time of the measurement

parameters.name: L
parameters.description: ---> Dipole L value calculated using the SM Reference Frame

parameters.name: L_Eq
parameters.description: ---> McElqain L value calculated at the Equator (derived from ECT MagEphem data).

parameters.name: L_Star
parameters.description: ---> Roeder's L* value (derived from ECT MagEphem data) for the average pitch angle.

parameters.name: I
parameters.description: ---> Integral invariant for the average pitch angle derived from ECT MagEphem data.

parameters.name: MLT
parameters.description: ---> Magnetic Local Time of S/C in Centerted Dipole Coordinates derived from ECT MagEphem data.

parameters.name: Position_TT
parameters.description: [Labels on plots] Position of the SC in the GEO Reference Frame.

parameters.name: Position_SM_TT
parameters.description: ---> [Labels on plots] Position of the spacecraft in SM coordinates

parameters.name: Position_GSM_TT
parameters.description: ---> [Labels on plots] Position of the SC in the GSM Reference Frame.

parameters.name: OrbitNumber_TT
parameters.description: [Labels on plots] Orbit Number at the time of the measurement

parameters.name: L_TT
parameters.description: ---> [Labels on plots] Dipole L value calculated using the SM Reference Frame

parameters.name: L_Eq_TT
parameters.description: ---> [Labels on plots] McElqain L value calculated at the Equator (derived from ECT MagEphem data).

parameters.name: L_Star_TT
parameters.description: ---> [Labels on plots] Roeder's L* value(derived from ECT MagEphem data) for the average pitch angle.

parameters.name: I_TT
parameters.description: ---> [Labels on plots] Integral invariant for the average pitch angle derived from ECT MagEphem data.

parameters.name: MLT_TT
parameters.description: ---> [Labels on plots] Magnetic Local Time of S/C in Centerted Dipole Coordinates derived from ECT MagEphem data.
